I called Roadside Assistance for a tow. Afterwards they connected me to GEARHART'S GARAGE INC.on Main St in Lake Elsinore,CA. Believe me, I truly was shaken to my core. All I could think about was I could have been trapped in that smoking car -I could have died & my family wouldnt have known where to find me. <Name>Peter Sterpe</Name>< Time>
1533227752216<//Time>
< rate>
5< /rate>
< text>
If you're staying in a neighborhood, and just finding a hotel room -- any hotel room -- is all that brought you there, you feel as if you won the lottery when you find a place like Sirens. As others have said, it's roomy, eclectic (local artists on the walls), chill, and welcoming. Very tasty cup of Costa Rican coffee, and the ham/egg/cheese croissant was better than any I have had -- a little toasty, enough to warm the fillings and melt the cheese, but not enough to dry out the croissant. The WiFi password is posted obviously -- that makes me feel as if it's OK to stay a while. I don't intent to park here, but it's the kind of place where the next great American novel could well be written. (And not by me -- ha!)
Very comfortable here, and will come again if my travels take me to San Pedro.< /text>

For a coffee house it is definitely high scale especially for the area of San Pedro that its in. And I hate to give a bad review, but I'll be honest. < review>
Friendly staff. If you want to park close you're going to have to pay the meter during the day. Wi-Fi only gives you 2 hours and get out afterwards. A little hard to figure out there WiFi you'll have to ask the friendly lady behind the counter how it works. Tea selection was good although I think they gave me the wrong tea. I asked for a lemon ginger and I think I got a Rooibos. Not crazy about coffee so I don't know anything about it. they had tons of Nibley little Goods that were freshly baked and they were amazing. This place is as big as a barn so there's plenty of seating for all. It has nice little nooks to add to the coziness and like home feeling. Electricity is hard to find for your laptop. Elsewise this place was clean beautiful and I would go here again with Mom for Saturday coffee.üç™<//review>

Had to go back and have her switch the prescription (another 30 min wait) and the new one was $100 which is still outrageous. I have had UTI's in the past and had antibiotics that were no more than $10. Clearly this dr is either an idiot or profiting from the prescriptions that she's prescribing.<//text>

< review>
This business is OUTSTANDING on all aspects of meticulous and perfect windshield repair, and very courteous and quick customer service. Thanks to Rick's "BEST OF THE BEST" expertise in windshield repair and his 30+ Years of priceless experience, that crack is now virtually INVISIBLE. After Rick's A+ repair, I can only find a BARELY visible and minor remnant of the cracked area, and I can only find that area IF I search for it very very closely. I do not see the crack at all while driving. CAUTION - - Because there are other businesses that use a name that is almost identical to the name of Rick's business, I made sure that I called "Santa Clarita Auto Glass" and I made sure that it is the business which has its ACTUAL OFFICE located in Valencia CA, at 28150 Avenue Crocker (located in a modern business park). I did a LOT of research on the various windshield repair businesses located in Santa Clarita-Valencia and in the adjacent San Fernando Valley.  After much research, Rick's business - - "Santa Clarita Auto Glass" - - was my clear choice. Rick truly cared about making sure that his repair work on my SUV's windshield was perfect, and it is. Rick is clearly THE MASTER at windshield repair, and he performed the repair as if he was repairing his own windshield. Rick's son Brian was very courteous, and Brian provided careful and attentive assistance throughout Rick's repair. They both provided me with "BEST OF THE BEST" windshield repair and customer service.  I have a 2nd SUV that I'll soon be bringing to them for windshield repair.  I would not rely on any other competing business for something as important as the structural safety of my windshield. Thank you Rick and Brian !<//review>

< review>
This business is OUTSTANDING on all aspects of meticulous and perfect windshield repair, and very courteous and quick customer service.  I had a VERY visible crack in my SUV's windshield - - possibly caused by a "BB" pellet. This was a big and very annoying visible crack directly in the line of sight. Thanks to Rick's "BEST OF THE BEST" expertise in windshield repair and his 30+ Years of priceless experience, that crack is now virtually INVISIBLE. After Rick's A+ repair, I can only find a BARELY visible and minor remnant of the cracked area, and I can only find that area IF I search for it very very closely. I do not see the crack at all while driving. CAUTION - - Because there are other businesses that use a name that is almost identical to the name of Rick's business, I made sure that I called "Santa Clarita Auto Glass" and I made sure that it is the business which has its ACTUAL OFFICE located in Valencia CA, at 28150 Avenue Crocker (located in a modern business park). I did a LOT of research on the various windshield repair businesses located in Santa Clarita-Valencia and in the adjacent San Fernando Valley.  After much research, Rick's business - - "Santa Clarita Auto Glass" - - was my clear choice. Rick truly cared about making sure that his repair work on my SUV's windshield was perfect, and it is. Rick is clearly THE MASTER at windshield repair, and he performed the repair as if he was repairing his own windshield. Rick's son Brian was very courteous, and Brian provided careful and attentive assistance throughout Rick's repair. They both provided me with "BEST OF THE BEST" windshield repair and customer service.  I have a 2nd SUV that I'll soon be bringing to them for windshield repair.  I would not rely on any other competing business for something as important as the structural safety of my windshield. Thank you Rick and Brian !</review>

<user>116528117830833143869</user><Name>Celestial Cat<//Name><time>1534489454308< /time><Rate>5</Rate><Text>I have rented storage space from a handful of companies over the years. Most places are all about the same . . . modest to modern offices, and rental spaces that consist of a metal door and ceiling, and three walls of drywall, decorated with plywood patches covering damaged drywall. They all charge close to the same rates for about the same services.

So I was skeptical when my realtor highly recommended US Storage on Foster Road in Norwalk, just because she had nothing but the highest praise for this location, where she stores her own personal stuff. If it weren't for the fact that she is also a dear friend, I would have suspected she was recommending it for a kickback.

The rent for the Public Storage room I had was going up 20% after only three months, despite the fact they had NOT indicated what I'd been paying was an introductory rate. So I knew I had to get out of there fast, and researched my friend's recommendation of US Storage online, and arranged to go in to rent a unit. I expected to see what I've always seen at storage places, so I was absolutely floored when I got there, and saw that it was everything my friend had said . . .

First impression was amazing! This place is huge, with the buildings facing the street decorated to look like pleasant housing or office parks so it doesn't look like an unsightly industrial block to mar the look of the neighborhood. Their office is modern and pleasant, and I was immediately greeted by the managers, Yvette and Filbert, who were very friendly, efficient, accommodating and informative. They did everything they could to make the transition easier, including the FREE use of their moving truck for the day!

Filbert took me out to the unit in a golf cart, and I could see their location is huge! Over 1,000 units! The area was neat and clean, and solar panels provide their electricity needs. Everything about the place told me it was well~planned and executed, corporate~run, not a franchise, and everything run to corporate standards!

THE BEST PART was seeing the unit itself! No pockmarked drywall with plywood decor! Wall to wall, floor to ceiling was clean corrugated metal walls, to keep the contents safe from being pilfered through through units! I loved that the units have ALARMS with a clever means of activation, and the doors have a locking system like nothing I've seen before, absolutely unbreakable. The unit looked brand new and well~sealed against pests.

All of this, and their prices are absolutely competitive with other companies! Now I understand my friend's excitement! Just like I was floored by my friend's recommendation, which seemed just impossible or at the very least, very exaggerated, now YOU're reading MY review and probably thinking the same thing. I assure you, prior to my friend's recommendation, I'd had NO knowledge of or affiliation with US Storage ~ Foster, and there is no monetary benefit for writing this review. I just wish I'd found them years ago, if there is anything I can do to send customers their way, AND also help YOU by recommending a great storage facility, I'm happy to do it! Life has enough complications, more things in life need to be this easy and worry~free!

:-) Have a lovely day!</Text>< pictures>
